Three v2→v3 deltas: `Context.Tag<T>()` becomes `Context.GenericTag<T>("scope/Name")`; the `Effect.Effect` type is now `<A, E, R>` (not `<R, E, A>`); and service access uses `yield* Tag`, not `Effect.service`.

```typescript
import { Effect, Context, Layer } from "effect";

interface Db {
  readonly query: (sql: string) => Effect.Effect<unknown[]>;
  readonly health: Effect.Effect<boolean>;
}

const Db = Context.GenericTag<Db>("app/Db");

const DbLive = Layer.succeed(Db, {
  query: (_sql) => Effect.succeed([]),
  health: Effect.succeed(true),
});

export const program: Effect.Effect<boolean, never, Db> = Effect.gen(function* () {
  const db = yield* Db;
  return yield* db.health;
});

export const runnable = program.pipe(Effect.provide(DbLive));
```

Health checks as a service method (rather than a free function) lets you fake them per-test and keep the program's `R` channel honest.

```typescript
import { Effect, Context, Layer } from "effect";

type FlagName = "dark-mode" | "beta-ui";

interface Flags {
  readonly isOn: (name: FlagName) => Effect.Effect<boolean>;
}

const Flags = Context.GenericTag<Flags>("app/Flags");

const FlagsLive = Layer.succeed(Flags, {
